AB  - By exposing the inconvenient truth of climate change, Al Gore has become one of the most celebrated advocates for ecological sustainability. Despite his prominence as an award-winning environmental rhetor, Gore has failed to achieve many of his primary reforms including a national super grid and carbon dioxide cap and trade system. From +An Inconvenient Truth: The Planetary Emergency of Global Warming and What We Can Do About It= to +Our Choice: How We Can Solve the Climate Crisis= to 'Climate of Denial: Can Science and the Truth Withstand the Merchants of Poison?', Gore's discourse is marked by a progressively angry and negative tone. In this dissertation, I examine the disconnections that contribute to this rising hostility and result in Gore's inability to realize climate change solutions. Although Gore's failure is partially due to his own weaknesses as a rhetor, his struggles elucidate the dilemmas of current conceptions of audience and agency. Citation reproduced with permission of ProQuest LLC. Abridged abstract reproduced with permission of ProQuest LLC. Full text available at URL below.
